      {
        "id": 2574594,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2019-02-01T13:38:51.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I tasted this twice from barrel and thought it was brilliant, better than either the 2007 or 2010 (the latter is not showing well in bottle, either, seems like it got a bit dried out) and nicely integrated despite its lavishness. I have a few bottles but haven\u2019t touched one yet so can\u2019t be any more help than that.</p>\n<p>The C\u00e9lestins I wish I owned a case of, however, is the 2008.</p>",
