      {
        "id": 2575032,
        "name": "Mark Golodetz",
        "username": "Mark_Golodetz",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/mark_golodetz/{size}/76850_2.png",
        "created_at": "2019-02-01T23:00:48.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"149589\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>I tasted this twice from barrel and thought it was brilliant, better than either the 2007 or 2010 (the latter is not showing well in bottle, either, seems like it got a bit dried out) and nicely integrated despite its lavishness. I have a few bottles but haven\u2019t touched one yet so can\u2019t be any more help than that.</p>\n<p>The C\u00e9lestins I wish I owned a case of, however, is the 2008.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>For me Celestins is best in the less ripe vintages.</p>\n<p>Totally agree with you about 2008, but have you tried the 2004?</p>",
        "post_number": 3,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 5,
