      {
        "id": 2575887,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2019-02-03T10:28:49.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"149589\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>For me Celestins is best in the less ripe vintages.</p>\n<p>Totally agree with you about 2008, but have you tried the 2004?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I love the 2004 but the 2008 is maybe a touch more precise. Never had them side by side though. In a riper register, 2005 and 2009 would be my favorites of the decade for him. But I think the wines became a bit less consistent from the mid-1990s on.</p>",
        "post_number": 4,
