      {
        "id": 2576023,
        "name": "Mark Golodetz",
        "username": "Mark_Golodetz",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/mark_golodetz/{size}/76850_2.png",
        "created_at": "2019-02-03T17:05:40.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Also never had them side by side. I have drunk practically a case of the 2004, but only once had the 2008, so although I see the resemblance, it is hard to make any definitive comparison.</p>\n<p>I do remember tasting a vertical of Celestins from 1978 to 1990. Favorites were the 1978, 1989 and 1986, but the 1990 was pruney but not nearly as bad as the 1990 reserve. The 2004 reminded me of the 1986.</p>",
